# 11. 引退

Airi: All right, that's good for today. You're really starting to improve.
Minori: Hehe. Thank you! I have you and Hinomori to thank for everything!
Airi: .....
Airi: Minori, have you seen Shizuku at all lately? I think she's been really busy with work. I haven't seen her at school.
Minori: I think she was here earlier this afternoon. One of my friends is a fan and said she saw her.
Airi: What? R-Really?
Minori: Y-Yeah. Is something wrong, Momoi?
Airi: ..... I kinda said something really terrible to her the other day.
Airi: She was worried about me, and I told her that everyone praises her as an idol without her barely having to do a thing.
Airi: So I want to apologize to her.
Minori: Wh-Why would you say something like that?
Airi: I think it's because I'm actually jealous of her.
Airi: We worked for the same agency, but Shizuku's always had so many of the things I wanted.
Airi: I was really surprised the first time I met her. Of course her looks were part of it, but she just had this quality about her. You couldn't help but look her way.
Airi: It was like she was born to be an idol. I felt totally defeated. I still promised myself I wouldn't lose, of course!
Airi: We both worked hard together until our debut. It was tough, but we helped each other get through it.
Airi: Then I started getting treated less and less like an idol, while Shizuku's career kept moving further ahead.
Airi: I kept thinking that if only I could be more like her... Oh, I'm such a terrible person...
Minori: Momoi...
Minori: Let's go find her so you can apologize, then! What do you say?
Airi: Sure. Thank you, Minori.
Minori: Let's check the classroom first, then—hm?
Minori: What's this? A notification from my news app?
Minori: What?! Momoi, this is terrible! Look!
Airi: Hm?
Classmate: That's it for classroom duty today.
Haruka: Okay. See you tomorrow.
Airi: Shizuku!
Haruka: Ah!
Haruka: Momoi? Why is she in such a hurry?
Minori: *Huff*... *Huff*... Oh, Haruka!
Haruka: You look flustered, too. What happened?
Minori: I-I just heard the news...
Haruka: !!
Breaking News:: <We have just learned that Shizuku Hinomori, lead of the popular group known as Cheerful*Days, has withdrawn from the group and left her agency.>
Airi: Stop right there, Shizuku!
Shizuku: Airi...
Airi: *Huff*... *Huff*...
Airi: So the rumors that you were planning on leaving Cheerful*Days were true? But why?
Shizuku: .....
Airi: Why won't you say something?! Tell me the truth, Shizuku!
Minori: Hinomori! Is it really true that you quit?
Shizuku: They told me they were going to wait a little longer before announcing it...
Haruka: Then it's true?
Shizuku: .....
Airi: Why, though?! There's absolutely no reason for you to quit being an idol!
Airi: You're so good that anybody would be jealous! You're beautiful and you have an aura about you that makes people turn your way just by standing there!
Shizuku: .....
Shizuku: Why do you have to say that?!
Airi: ...What?
Shizuku: You were the one who taught me that having heart was the most important thing.
Shizuku: That an idol is someone who gives hope to their fans.
Shizuku: That's why I've tried so hard all this time to become that kind of idol. But now...
Shizuku: But now everyone attacks me, talking about my looks or how I was born to be an idol and don't have to work for it!
Airi: !!
Airi: Did you quit because of me?
Airi: Because of what I said?
Shizuku: Well...
Shizuku: I've...been thinking about quitting for a while now. Ever since things started falling apart with the others.
Haruka: The others? You mean the other members of Cheerful*Days?
Haruka: Does that mean the rumors of them being jealous of you were true?
Shizuku: .....
Shizuku: It wasn't like that at first. We used to have fun competing and pushing each other to work harder.
Shizuku: Everything changed once I started being the center. It began to seem like the selection process for choosing the center was just formality.
Shizuku: It seemed like no matter how hard the others worked, I was the only one getting more job offers. They started to grow distant.
Haruka: I see...
Shizuku: I tried to smooth things over so we could keep working together, but there was only so much I could do...
Shizuku: I don't even know if I still like being an idol.
Airi: !!
Airi: It's my fault...
Airi: I was supposed to give others hope, but instead I did the exact opposite.
Airi: I stole your love of being an idol.
Minori: Momoi...
Airi: No... Please, Shizuku. You're a true idol. You're not like me, Shizuku.
Airi: I can't just stand by and watch this happen!!
Minori: M-Momoi! Where are you going?!
Haruka: I'll bet she went to the Cheerful*Days theater.
Minori: What?!
